<br>
  While I will agree all is fair in war, this statement here is a little bit shortsighted to say the least.  Countries of this world after having witnessed firsthand the destruction of the 2nd world war decided to put an end (or at least try) to the senseless carnage that came about from purposefully targetting civilians.  <br>
<br>
  You could speak till you're blue in the face but I'd find it hard for any person to realistically explain how the garbage man who was on the 32nd floor was a military combatant.  Now if as you state the guy picked up a rifle and a home made bomb, then yes, he's ascended from the innocent civilian stage to the partisan stage and as such is fair game.  Just killing everyone from the opposing nation no matter who they are, what they do etc... is generally referred to as Genocide.<br>
<br>
  Heck according to your concept of warfare, our best strategy to win the war in Iraq was just to Nuke every city they had.  We win!<br>
