<br>
The entire airline industry was devastated for years (and is still reeling from the blow).  That it pursuaded people to stay away from that method of economic commerce for so long makes it an even bigger success.<br>
<br>
The economy of the entire nation was adversely affected much more so than if, say, a massive bomb had destroyed an entire army base.<br>
<br>
That people are now leery of doing business in large buildings means a further hit to the economy, since most large financial institutions are headquartered in large buildings.<br>
<br>
It was a direct attack upon the economic infrastructure of the US.  Warfare is the armed conflict between two economies.<br>
<br>
Causing long-lasting fear in the populace does not diminish the scale of the Act of War.  Instead, it dramatically increases it.<br>
